Content:
they can do everything, even banning it - but unless they realize they cant "control" it, they wont  since it would be counterproductive for "them". 
If you control 100% of the tech. infrastructure (ISP, DNS, etc.), 100% of the legal base/legislation, 100% of the currency that 99.9% of the crypto-hodlers trade crypto against, and and and. then well, why would you want to destroy or harm crypto as such - you already indirectly "control" it. 
So could be def. much more lucrative/target-aimed to instead take the control over of all the other underlying tech/base. 
"You can destroy something just by building up something else" - even very constructive energy that looks positive can result in huge destructive power and negative results.
